[0.039, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mTwo\u001b[7Gkinds\u001b[13Gof\u001b[16Grough edge are worth capturing in their own file for filing upstream — don't quietly work around either:\r\u001b[2C\u001b[2BIf you hit a\u001b[16Gc\u001b[18Gmpil\u001b[23Gr bug, minimize i\u001b[41G f\u001b[44Grst: bis\u001b[53Gct\u001b[56Gto the smallest source \u001b[80Ghat still triggers it, and find the \u001b[39m    \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mclosest variant that *does* compile, so the trigger is pinned down precisely (not just \"my big program failed\"). Then\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bwrite it \u001b[13Go a `BUG-<slug>.md` file in the project roo\u001b[57G with\u001b[63Ga one-line title, the `promise v\u001b[98Gion`\u001b[103Goutput, your\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bp\u001b[5Gatform, the minimal repro\u001b[31G(s\u001b[34Gal\u001b[38Gst `.pr`\u001b[47Gsourc\u001b[53G plus the exact `\u001b[72Gom\u001b[77G build`\u001b[85Gcommand), the verb\u001b[104Gtim error \u001b[39m      \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255moutput, the\u001b[15Gexpected behavior, a short table of what does and\u001b[65Gdo\u001b[68Gsn't tr\u001b[76Ggg\u001b[79Gr\u001b[81Git,\u001b[85Gyour best guess at the cause, and \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe w\u001b[10Gkaround you used in the real code. Ver"]
[0.000, "o", "ify the repro actually fail\u001b[76G and the\u001b[85G\"co\u001b[89Gpiles\u001b[95Gfine\" con\u001b[105Grols actually \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcom\u001b[7Gile\u001b[11Gbefore writing them down\u001b[36G— don'\u001b[43G go from memory.\u001b[39m                                                            \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B                                                                                                                    \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mIf the task n\u001b[17Geds something\u001b[31GPromise doesn't\u001b[47Ghave\u001b[52Gy\u001b[54Gt — a standard-library module that isn't there, or a missing \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blanguage feature — don't fake it silently. Build the closest clean thing you can, or, if it's a hard blocker, stop \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Band say why. Either way record the gap i\u001b[44G a\u001b[47G`FEATURE-<slug>.m\u001b[65G` fi\u001b[70Ge in the project root: a\u001b[95Gon\u001b[98G-line title, the\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B`promis\u001b[12Gv\u001b[14Grsion` outpu\u001b[27G, what you n\u001b[40Geded and why the ta\u001b[60Gk cal\u001b[67Gd for it, what's missing\u001b[92G(e.g. no standard module for\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BX, no language support for Y),\u001b[34Gw\u001b[37Gther\u001b[43Gt\u001b[45Gblocked you"]
[0.000, "o", " outright or just forced a workar\u001b[90Gund,\u001b[95Gth\u001b[98G workaround you used,\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Band — if\u001b[12Gyou ca\u001b[19G — a **sketch of the API or syntax** th\u001b[59Gt wou\u001b[65Gd have made\u001b[77Git clean.\u001b[39m                                  \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B                                                                                                                    \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mPut\u001b[7G`Please file\u001b[20Gthis upstream at \u001b[38Gttps://github.com/promise-\u001b[65Ganguage/prom\u001b[78Gse/issues` at the top of any such file, \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bwrite one file per distinct issue, and mention each in your summary so I remember to submit it. Only write these for \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Breal failures and real gaps — don't invent them.\u001b[39m                                                                   \r\u001b[1B\u001b[49m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m⏺\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[23C\u001b[2B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mthought for 7s)\u001b[39m\u001b[30;1H\u001b[28;3H"]
