[0.156, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mclosest variant that *does* comp\u001b[36Gl\u001b[38G, so the trigg\u001b[53Gr is pinned down precisely (not just\u001b[90G\"my big progr\u001b[104Gm fa\u001b[109Gled\").\u001b[116GThen\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bwrit\u001b[8G it to \u001b[16G `BUG-<slug>.md` file in the project \u001b[54Goot\u001b[58Gw\u001b[60Gth a\u001b[65Gone-lin\u001b[73G tit\u001b[78Ge, the\u001b[85G`promise\u001b[94Gversion` output, your\u001b[116G\u001b[39m    \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mpla\u001b[7Gform, the\u001b[17Gminimal repro (sma\u001b[36Glest\u001b[41G`.pr` source plus the\u001b[63Gexact `promise build`\u001b[85Gcommand), the verbatim error \u001b[39m  \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255moutput, the \u001b[16Gxpected behavior, \u001b[35G short table \u001b[49Gf what does and doesn't trigger it,\u001b[85Gy\u001b[87Gur best\u001b[95Ggu\u001b[98Gss at \u001b[105Ghe\u001b[108Gcause, and \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe workaround you used in the\u001b[34Greal code. V\u001b[47Gri\u001b[50Gy the\u001b[56Grepro actually fails and\u001b[81Gthe\u001b[85G\"compiles\u001b[95Gfine\"\u001b[101Gcon\u001b[105Grols actually\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcompile before\u001b[18Gwriting them down — don't go from\u001b[52Gmemo\u001b[57Gy.\u001b[39m                                                      "]
[0.000, "o", "      \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B                                                        \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mIf the task needs something Promise doesn't have yet — a standard-library module that isn't there, or a missing \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blanguage feature — don't fake it \u001b[37Gilently. Build\u001b[52Gthe\u001b[56Gclosest clean thing you can, or,\u001b[90Gf i\u001b[94G's a hard blocker, stop \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Band s\u001b[9Gy why. Either way record \u001b[35Ghe gap in a `FEATURE-<slug>.md` file \u001b[74G the project root: a one-line\u001b[104Gtitle, the \u001b[39m   \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m`promise version` output, what\u001b[34Gyou\u001b[38Gneeded\u001b[46Gnd why the task called for it, what's missing (e.g. no standard module for\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BX, no language support for Y),\u001b[34Gwheth\u001b[40Gr it\u001b[45Gblocked\u001b[53Gyou\u001b[57Goutright or\u001b[69Gjust forced a workaround, the work\u001b[104Groun\u001b[110Gy\u001b[112Gu used,\u001b[39m \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mand —\u001b[9Gif you can — a **sketch of the API or syntax** tha\u001b[60G would have made it clean.\u001b[39m                                 \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B                            "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                       \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mPut `Please file this upstream at https://github.com/promise-language/promise/issues` at the top of any such file, \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bwrite one file per distinct issue, and ment\u001b[47Gon ea\u001b[53Gh in your summary so I rem\u001b[80Gmber to submit i\u001b[97G. Only write these for \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Breal failures and real gaps\u001b[31G— don't invent them.\u001b[39m                                                                     \r\u001b[1B\u001b[49m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m⏺\u001b[3G\u001b[39mI'll\u001b[8Gstart\u001b[14Gby\u001b[17Gunderstanding\u001b[31Gthe\u001b[35Gcurrent\u001b[43Gstate\u001b[49Gof\u001b[52Gthe\u001b[56Gworking\u001b[64Gdirectory\u001b[74Gand\u001b[78Glearning\u001b[87GPromise\u001b[95Gfrom\u001b[100Gthe\u001b[104Gtoolchain.\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m⏺\u001b[3G\u001b[39mRunning\u001b[11G\u001b[1m2\u001b[13G\u001b[22mshell\u001b[19Gcommands…\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m  ⎿  $ pwd && ls -la && echo \"---GIT---\" && git status && echo \"---PROMISE---\" && promise version\u001b[39m\u001b[30;1H\u001b[28;3H"]
[0.018, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mIf you hit a compiler bug, minimize it first: bisect to the smallest source that still triggers it, and find the \u001b[39m     \r\u001b[24B\u001b[49m\u001b[38;2;215;119;87m✶\u001b[3G\u001b[38;2;235;159;127mP\u001b[6G\u001b[38;2;215;119;87mc\u001b[20G\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m1\u001b[28G75\u001b[39m\u001b[30;1H\u001b[28;3H"]
