[0.017, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255moutput, the expected behavior, a short table of what does and doesn't trigger it, your best guess at the cause, and \u001b[39m  \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mthe w\u001b[10Gkaround you used in the real code. Verify the repro actually fail\u001b[76G and the\u001b[85G\"co\u001b[89Gpiles\u001b[95Gfine\" con\u001b[105Grols actually \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcom\u001b[7Gile\u001b[11Gbefore writing them down\u001b[36G— don'\u001b[43G go from memory.\u001b[39m                                                            \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B                                                                                                                    \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mIf the task n\u001b[17Geds something\u001b[31GPromise doesn't\u001b[47Ghave\u001b[52Gy\u001b[54Gt — a standard-library module that isn't there, or a missing \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blanguage feature — don't fake it silently. Build the closest clean thing you can, or, if it's a hard blocker, stop \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Band say why. Either way record the gap i\u001b[44G a\u001b[47G`FEATURE-<slug>.m\u001b[65G` fi\u001b[70Ge in the project root: a\u001b[95Gon\u001b[98G-line"]
