[0.103, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                        \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mIf the task needs something Promise doesn't have yet — a standard-library module that isn't there, or a missing \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blanguage feature — don't fake it \u001b[37Gilently. Build\u001b[52Gthe\u001b[56Gclosest clean thing you can, or,\u001b[90Gf i\u001b[94G's a hard blocker, stop \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Band s\u001b[9Gy why. Either way record \u001b[35Ghe gap in a `FEATURE-<slug>.md` file \u001b[74G the project root: a one-line\u001b[104Gtitle, the \u001b[39m   \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m`promise version` output, what\u001b[34Gyou\u001b[38Gneeded\u001b[46Gnd why the task called for it, what's missing (e.g. no standard module for\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BX, no language support for Y),\u001b[34Gwheth\u001b[40Gr it\u001b[45Gblocked\u001b[53Gyou\u001b[57Goutright or\u001b[69Gjust forced a workaround, the work\u001b[104Groun\u001b[110Gy\u001b[112Gu used,\u001b[39m \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mand —\u001b[9Gif you can — a **sketch of the API or syntax** tha\u001b[60G would have made it clean.\u001b[39m                                 \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B            "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                       \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mPut `Please file this upstream at https://github.com/promise-language/promise/issues` at the top of any such file, \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bwrite one file per distinct issue, and ment\u001b[47Gon ea\u001b[53Gh in your summary so I rem\u001b[80Gmber to submit i\u001b[97G. Only write these for \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Breal failures and real gaps\u001b[31G— don't invent them.\u001b[39m                                                                     \r\u001b[1B\u001b[49m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m⏺\u001b[3G\u001b[39mI'll\u001b[8Gstart\u001b[14Gby\u001b[17Gunderstanding\u001b[31Gthe\u001b[35Gcurrent\u001b[43Gstate\u001b[49Gof\u001b[52Gthe\u001b[56Gworking\u001b[64Gdirectory\u001b[74Gand\u001b[78Glearning\u001b[87GPromise\u001b[95Gfrom\u001b[100Gthe\u001b[104Gtoolchain.\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mRan \u001b[1m2\u001b[22m shell commands \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m⏺\u001b[3G\u001b[39mThis\u001b[8Gis\u001b[11Ga\u001b[13Gre-record\u001b[23G(toolchain\u001b[34Gmoved\u001b[40Gto\u001b[43G2026.1).\u001b[52GThe\u001b[56Grun\u001b[60Gdir\u001b[64Gwas\u001b[68Gwiped,\u001b[75Gleaving\u001b[83Gonly\u001b[88G\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mcontext.md\u001b[99G\u001b[39mand\u001b"]
[0.000, "o", "[103G\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mdemo.cast\u001b[39m.\u001b[114GLet\u001b[118Gme\r\u001b[1B \u001b[3Gc\u001b[5Geck context and learn Prom\u001b[32Gse.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mRead \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m file, ran \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m shell command \r\u001b[1B  ⎿  $ git show HEAD:mini-git/mini-git-claude/SUMMARY.md 2>/dev/null | head -60 || echo \"no prior summary at that path\"\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m⏺\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[40C\u001b[2B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mthought for 4s)\u001b[39m\u001b[30;1H\u001b[28;3H"]
